post_text:
Parents and Students

After the first 8 days of school we are making some changes going forward for our 5-12 students.
Students will still remain with their grade level peers during the school day, be expected to wear a mask and socially distance when possible.
However, starting on Tuesday 9/8/2020 they will have opportunities to leave their homeroom during the week to go to Shop, Art, Music and PE if they have those classes.
This is a change that teachers and administration feel is in the best interest of student learning and our students have expressed excitement to get into those hands-on classes to learn.

Thank you for your understanding and support,

Christopher Mothorn
5-12 Principal
Darby School District
Go Tigers!

post_text: There seems to be an inaccurate rumor going around in regards to how we will be handling a student who may need to be quarantined. We are NOT quarantining any student at school. Students who do show flu like symptoms will be sent to the office where the building Secretary will contact parents to have them pick the student up. It is the parents responsibility to have their child tested and quarantined for the appropriate time frame before returning to school. Parents will have limited access to our school unless it's an emergency. If you have any other questions or concerns please contact our High School (406) 821-3252 or Elementary/JH (406) 821-3643.

post_text:
Darby School Board Vacancy
The Darby Board of Trustees is currently accepting applications to fill a vacancy due to the resignation of a board member. This position will be filled by appointment by the board until the next regular school district election in May 2021. The appointee will then be voted on by the public to continue this three year seat. Applications will be accepted until September 7, 2020. The board will interview up to five candidates at the next regular meeting on September 14, 2020. Any person qualified to vote in the Darby School district is eligible for the office of trustee. Please send an application to: Darby School, Atten: Lisa Poe, 209 School Drive, Darby, MT 59829 or email to lpoe@darby.k12.mt.us if you are interested in serving on the Darby School Board. Applications can be found on our website www.darby.k12.mt.us or at the High School Office.

Ravalli County Public Health

Calling for Volunteers: (406) 375-6672
Ravalli county public health is setting up a volunteer "pool" to help people in need. We are looking for Volunteers that meet the following requirements:
1) Between the ages of 18 -25
2) Have their own transportation
3) Live in a house hold with no dependents or older "at risk" house mates
4) Are available to work several hours and want to be part of the solution!

Award Winning Film To Be Shown Tonight During Mid-Winter Fair in Hays

MAPS Media Institute
February 8 at 10:31 AM ·

Thank you Blaine County Journal and Donna Miller for this fantastic write up about the inspiring staff and students in Harlem, MT and their powerful, award-winning collaborations with MAPS.

We look forward to celebrating with the Harlem Team at the screening of "Looking Forward From Yesterday" at the Big Sky Documentary Film Festival on Tuesday, February 18, 4pm as part of the Schoolhouse Docs block hosted at the Zootown Arts Center, 216 West Main in Missoula.

Thank you Greater Montana Foundation and Montana GEAR UP for your generous investment to help bring this story to screen. #investinginMontanasfuture
